Calicivirus, school outbreak - Canada (Alberta) 20010517.0965
Date: Fri 18 May 2001 11:30:09 +0300
From: Stephen Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GIDEON Database, Fri 18 May 2001 [edited
<http://www.cyinfo.com>

Background Information on Viral Gastroenteritis in Canada
---------------------------------------------------------
In total, 44 laboratory reports of calicivirus infection were registered in
1996; 17 in 1997.
In 1997, 6 outbreaks of calicivirus infection (163 cases) were reported; 11
(64 cases) in 1998.
An outbreak of calicivirus infection (48 cases) at a restaurant in Quebec
in 1998 was traced to a food-handler.
In 1996, a total of 89 laboratory reports of astrovirus infection were
registered; 41 in 1997. Also in 1996, there were 589 laboratory reports of
Norwalk virus registered; 468 in 1997.
Rotavirus accounted for 32% of childhood viral diarrhea in Ontario during
November 1997 to June 1998; adenovirus 4%; torovirus 3%; Norwalk-like
viruses 2%; astrovirus and calicivirus < 1%.
--
Stephen Berger
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
